 VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}]}}}